Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a specific data structure, the Burrows-Wheeler transform, which is commonly used in text compression and indexing, further supporting the classification of the paper in the data structures category. The paper also discusses the use of Markovian corrections, which are commonly used in machine learning and natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or data mining (cs.DM) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of multiple values of k, which is a common technique in bioinformatics, suggesting that it could also belong to the databases (cs.DB) category.
